{'html': '\n<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN">\n<html>\n  <head>\n    <title>COMP M074/GV14 &ndash; Home</title>\n    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=iso-8859-1" />\n    <meta name="robots" content="noindex,nofollow,noarchive">\n    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" type="text/css" />\n    <script type="text/javascript" src="hiddenemail.js"></script>\n  </head>\n\n  <body>\n    <!-- <h1>COMP M074/GV14 &ndash; Home</h1> -->\n    <h1>Advanced Modelling, Rendering and Animation</h1>\n    <h2>Home</h2>\n\n      Home | <a href="syllabus.php">Syllabus</a> | <a href="coursework.php">Course Work</a> | <a href="assessment.php">Assessment</a>      <p/>\n\n<table width="100%" cellpadding=6 cellspacing=1 bgcolor="#a0a0b0" >\n<tr bgcolor="#e8e8f0">\n<th align=left><font size=\\"+2\\">General Information</font></th>\n</tr>\n<tr bgcolor="#ffffff"> <td> \n<p>\n<table width="100%" cellpadding=6 cellspacing=1>\n  <tr>\n  <th align=right valign=top><font size="-1">Description:</font></th>\n  <td>\n  The overall aim of this course is to teach the principles of modelling and rendering for the production of photorealistic images. By the end of this course students should have a firm understanding of advanced rendering techniques, including global illumination techniques, methods for real-time graphics, and image based approaches. Students will also be able to understand techniques for advanced modeling, including constructive solid geometry and B-Spline techniques. Finally students will have an introduction to physical and character-based animation techniques.<br>\n  See the <a href="syllabus.php">syllabus page</a> for the general course structure.\n  </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n  <th align=right valign=top><font size="-1">Prerequisites:</font></th>\n  <td>\n  It is assumed that the students have already taken an introductory graphics course or 3080/GV10.\n  </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n  <th align=right valign=top><font size="-1">Assessment:</font></th>\n  <td>\n  The assessment will be based on two course works and a written examination. See <a href="assessment.php">here</a> for more information.\n  </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n  <th align=right valign=top><font size="-1">Lecturers:</font></th>\n  <td>\n  <script type="text/javascript">hiddenemail(\'cs.ucl.ac.uk\',\'t.weyrich\',\'Tim Weyrich\')</script>,\n  <script type="text/javascript">hiddenemail(\'cs.ucl.ac.uk\',\'j.kautz\',\'Jan Kautz\')</script> and\n  <script type="text/javascript">hiddenemail(\'gmail.com\',\'panxueni\',\'Xueni "Sylvia" Pan\')</script><noscript>Tim Weyrich, Jan Kautz and Xueni "Sylvia" Pan</noscript>.\n  </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n  <th align=right valign=top><font size="-1">Demonstrator:</font></th>\n  <td>\n  <script type="text/javascript">hiddenemail(\'cs.ucl.ac.uk\',\'f.pece\',\'Fabrizio Pece\')</script><noscript>Fabrizio Pece</noscript>.\n  </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n  <th align=right valign=top><font size="-1">Time&amp;Place:</font></th>\n  <td>\n  <b>Mon:</b> 2&ndash;4pm (Foster Court 132);<br>\n  <b>Wed:</b> 10&ndash;11am (Foster Court 114).\n  <br>\n  Practicals will be Fridays, 2&ndash;4pm, room MPEB 1.05. <b>The first practical will take place on 25<sup>th</sup> January.</b>\n  \n  </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n  <th align=right valign=top><font size="-1">Mailing Lists:</font></th>\n  <td>\n  The module uses the mailing list provided through UCL\'s Moodle system.\n  </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n  <th align=right valign=top><font size="-1">Past Exams:</font></th>\n  <td>\n  Past years\' exam papers are available through <a href="http://www.ucl.ac.uk/Library/exam.shtml">UCL Library</a>. <i><b>Note (5 Feb 2013):</b></i> as of to date, the most recent exam (2012) has not yet been made available by the library, so we are posting it <a href="./exams/exam-2012-COMPGV14-questions.pdf">here</a>.\n  </td>\n  </tr>\n\n  <tr>\n  <th align=right valign=top valign=top><font size="-1">Readings:</font></th>\n  <td>\n<p><b>Main Reading</b></p>\n<p>\nComputer Graphics And Virtual Environments - From Realism to Real-Time. Mel Slater, Yiorgos Chrysanthou, Anthony Steed, ISBN 0201-62420-6, Addison-Wesley, 2002. (See <a href="http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/staff/a.steed/book_tmp/CGVE/">http://www.cs.ucl.ac.uk/staff/a.steed/book_tmp/CGVE/</a>.)\n<p><b>Additional Reading</b></p>\n<p>\nJ Foley, A van Dam, SK Feiner, JF Hughes, RR Phillips, Introduction to Computer Graphics, Addison-Wesley, 1994, ISBN 0-201-60921-5.<br>\n\nNik Lever, Realtime 3D Character animation with Visual C++, Morgan-Kaufmann, 2002, ISBN 0240516648.<br>\n\nAlan Watt, Mark Watt Advanced Animation and Rendering Techniques: Theory and Practice, Addison Wesley Professional, ISBN 0-201-54412-1, 1992.<br>\n\nFrancois X. Sillion and Claude Puech, Radiosity and Global Illumination, Morgan Kaufmann Publishers, San Francisco, 1994. ISBN 1-55860-277-1.<br>\n    </p>\n<p><b>Additional Demos and Resources</b></p>\n<p>\n<ul>\n <li>\n     GPUs</li>\n <ul>\n  <li><a\n      href="http://mew.cx/glsl/shadergen/">ShaderGen and GLSL\n      Demo</a> from 3D Labs</li>\n\n  <li><a\n      href="http://developer.nvidia.com/object/fx_composer_home.html">FX\n      Composer 2.5</a> from NVidia</li>\n  <li><a\n      href="Misc/specular.zip">Basic Per-Vertex Per-Pixel Lighting Demo</a>\n      from Anthony Steed</li>\n </ul>\n <li>\n     Texture Mapping and Texture Generation</li>\n\n <ul>\n  <li><a\n      href="http://usa.autodesk.com/adsk/servlet/pc/index?id=11390028&siteID=123112">Adobe Image Modeler</a> and the example 3D model of a <a href="Misc/test.wrl">pinball\n      machine</a></li>\n  <li><a\n      href="http://www.debevec.org/Campanile/">The Campanile video</a> by Paul\n      Debevec</li>\n </ul>\n <li>\n\n     Surfaces</li>\n <ul>\n  <li><a\n      href="http://www.nigels.com/research/">Real-Time CSG</a></li>\n  <li><a\n      href="http://k3dsurf.sourceforge.net/">Surface Visualisation</a><o:p></o:p></li>\n </ul>\n</ul>\n    </p>\n  </td>\n  </tr>\n  </table>\n</tr>\n</table>\n\n    <p/>\n    <address><script type="text/javascript">hiddenemail(\'cs.ucl.ac.uk\',\'t.weyrich\')</script>\n      <noscript>enable java script to see my email address</noscript></address>\n  </body>\n</html>\n',
